** Introduction

Responsive Design is when you make it so a web page can dynamically change size to fit the screen
For example, whether your looking at a web page on a PC or an iPhone

You can use units, 15vh -> as you change size of the screen the box will dynamically always be 15 pixels away from the top of the screen

** Tags & Units

*Tags*

.element {
          position: static;
}

position can have the values: static, relative, absolute & fixed
static -> elements are positioned to normal document flow
relative -> elements are positioned relative to original position
absolute -> elements are positioned relative to their nearest ancestor
fixed -> elements are positioned relative to the viewport

*Units*

vw = vertical width (in percent, i.e 70vh will mean the element always takes up 70% of the viewport height)
vh = vertical height (in percent)

em = relative unit based on the font size of the parent
rem = relative unit based on the font size of the root

** Breakpoint

Setting elements so if the page goes too large or too small, they will adjust their size

You can add a minimum, maximum & optimum size that the element should adhere to

** Flexbox & Grid

These are built-in CSS layout systems

Flexbox -> 1D, works with a row or a column but not both
Grid    -> 2D, lets you control both directions at the same time

*Flexbox*

Use Flexbox when you are arranging items in 1 direction (for example, a logo next to a link next to a button)

.container {
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
}

All elements above with the class "container" will be horizontally in order & centered

Result:

    | Item 1 |
    | Item 2 |
    | Item 3 |

*Grid*

Use Grid for arranging items that need to sit next to each other & go vertically down the page (i.e. product sale)

.products {
           display: grid;
           grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
           gap: 20;
}

All items with the class "products" will be organised 3 horizontally, with each item getting 1 fraction of space (equal)

Result:

| Item | Item | Item |
| Item | Item | Item |


