ARIA (Accessible Rich Internet Applications) -> an attribute you add to an element for screen readers
For example -> adding alt to an <img> which screen readers can read out

The majority of 'Accessibility' in html is just using Semantic elements
But sometimes adding ARIA tags in specific places is useful

