** HTML format

You need to add the link to the Bootstrap website in the <head> but before the CSS linker
Otherwise, Bootstrap gets confused & can't read the CSS

You also need a linker line at the bottom of the page before the end of <body>

The <link> (one in the <head>) loads a stylesheet which gives the page Bootstrap's pre-made CSS rules
The <script> (one at the end of <body>) tells the browser to load & run this JS file, which points to Bootstraps JS library

An alternative to this is to download Bootstrap into your project, next to the index.html & style.css

** Summary

1. *container*
   Creates a centered page wrapper with responsive widths

2. *row*
   Goes within a container
   Creates a horizontal group of 12 columns

3. *col-md-6*
   Goes within a row
   Create a column, apply this rule at medium screens, take up 6 of 12 grid spaces

4. *mb-4*
   Margin bottom with spacing 4 (0 = no spacing, 3 = medium & 5 = largest)
   Goes after col-md-6 to signify, after this column add x spacing below

5. *img-fluid*
   Makes images responsive
   Goes with <img>

6. *btn*
   Activates Bootstrap button styling
   Goes within <button>
   btn-primary or -warning or -info don't change anything other than the colour
   btn-link makes it look like a link instead of a button

7. *form-control*
   Adds better sizing, padding, border styling, etc... within a form
   Used within <input>
   
8. *col-form-label*
   Makes labels align nicely inside grid forms, by formatting it next to the input
   Used within <label>


